<title>USA: Striker sues over breach of merger pact.</title>
<headline>Striker sues over breach of merger pact.</headline>
<dateline>HOUSTON 1997-04-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Striker Industries Inc said Thursday it filed suit against Newgen Holdings Inc, Gen Holdings Inc, GS Roofing Products Co Inc and others for alleged breach of binding agreements involving a merger deal between it and the defendants.</p>
<p>In its lawsuit, Striker alleged that the defendants' wrongful repudiation of the agreements severely impaired its ability to complete the equity and debt offerings that were critical to the transaction.</p>
<p>Striker said protracted negotiations between the parties to attempt to reinstate the transaction have been unsuccessful to date.</p>
</text>
